MRS spectral leak correction¶

In this notebook we derive a correction for the spectral leak present in MRS band 3A detector images (see MIRI-TN-00002-KUL written by Dr. Bart Vandenbussche).

MIRI-TN-00002-KUL section 2: The MRS spectrometers are designed to cover the respective spectral band wavelength ranges in the first spectral order. A diffraction grating will yield maximum constructive interference for light of wavelength in the first order at an exit angle . At the same exit angle maximum constructive interference will also be seen for light of wavelength /2 (second order), /3 (third order), etc... Without a proper pre-selection of the wavelength bandpass entering the spectrometer, (parts of) these higher order spectra will be superimposed on the first order spectrum.

Such an occurence is expected to happen in MRS band 3A due to a spectral leakage from the dichroic transmission in band 1B. This is shown below.

Remarks:¶

  • The spectral leak of 2.8% at 6.1 micron will affect the MRS spectrum at 12.2 microns.

The contribution of the two spectral orders is disentagle as prescribed in MIRI-TN-00002-KUL. The result is shown below.

In [6]:
# Populate dictionaries with the wavelength, pixel size and validity maps 
# (corresponding to the detector plane)

sliceMap  = {}
sizeMap   = {}
validMap  = {}
lambdaMap = {}

for band in bands:
    d2cMaps         = funcs.load_obj('d2cMaps_band{}'.format(band),path=d2cMapDir)
    sliceMap[band]  = d2cMaps['sliceMap']
    lambdaMap[band] = d2cMaps['lambdaMap']
    sizeMap[band]   = funcs.get_pixel_spatial_area(band=band,d2cMaps=d2cMaps)
    
    # create a "valid" map with all the pixels inside the slices of a particular band
    channel = int(band[0])
    # slice numbers in the slice map of the distortion CDP for this band
    sliceInventory = np.unique(sliceMap[band])
    slicesInBand = sliceInventory[np.where( (sliceInventory >= 100*channel ) & (sliceInventory <100*(channel+1)))]
    
    validMap[band] = np.zeros(sliceMap[band].shape)
    for ss in slicesInBand:
        s = int(ss - 100*channel)
        # construct a list of y,x coordinates of detector pixels belonging to slices of this band
        pixels = np.where(sliceMap[band] == ss)
        validMap[band][pixels] = 1
In [7]:
# Populate dictionaries with maps of L_sky
L_skyMap = {}
for BBTemp in ["400K", "600K", "800K"]:
    L_skyMap[BBTemp] = {}   
    tabLSky = fits.open(MTSDir+ "MTSEquivalentLsky" + BBTemp + ".fits" )[1]
    ip_Lsky = scp_interpolate.interp1d(tabLSky.data["wave"], tabLSky.data["L_sky"], kind='cubic')
    for band in bands:
        L_skyMap[BBTemp][band] = np.full( validMap[band].shape, np.nan )
        sel = (validMap[band]==1)
        waves = np.reshape(lambdaMap[band][sel], -1)
        L_skyMap[BBTemp][band][sel] = ip_Lsky(waves)*1000. #mJy/arcsec^2
In [8]:
# Populate dictionaries with maps of E_pix
# Calculate the spectral irradiance E_pix : [mJy/pixel]
# E_pix = omega_pix * L_pix
E_pixMap = {}
for BBTemp in ["400K", "600K", "800K"]:
    E_pixMap[BBTemp] = {}
    for band in bands:
        E_pixMap[BBTemp][band] = np.full( validMap[band].shape, np.nan )
        sel = (validMap[band]==1)
        E_pixMap[BBTemp][band][sel] = sizeMap[band][sel] * L_skyMap[BBTemp][band][sel]
In [9]:
EXTSOURCE_pixMap = {}
for BBTemp in ["400K", "600K", "800K"]:
    EXTSOURCE_pixMap[BBTemp] = {}
    for band in bands:
        EXTSOURCE_SCI_pixMap,EXTSOURCE_BKG_pixMap = mrsobs.FM_MTS_BB_extended_source(lvl2path,band,bb_temp=BBTemp,output='img')
        EXTSOURCE_pixMap[BBTemp][band] = EXTSOURCE_SCI_pixMap-EXTSOURCE_BKG_pixMap
In [10]:
interp_EXTSOURCE_pixMap = {}
interp_E_pixMap         = {}
for BBTemp in ["400K", "600K", "800K"]:
    interp_EXTSOURCE_pixMap[BBTemp] = {}
    interp_E_pixMap[BBTemp]         = {}
    for band in bands:
        d2cMaps   = funcs.load_obj('d2cMaps_band{}'.format(band),path=d2cMapDir)
        ypos,xpos = funcs.detpixel_trace(band,d2cMaps,sliceID=d2cMaps['nslices']/2,alpha_pos=0.)
        sel       = (lambdaMap[band][ypos,xpos]!=0) & (~np.isnan(EXTSOURCE_pixMap[BBTemp][band][ypos,xpos]))
        interp_EXTSOURCE_pixMap[BBTemp][band] = scp_interpolate.interp1d(lambdaMap[band][ypos,xpos][sel],EXTSOURCE_pixMap[BBTemp][band][ypos,xpos][sel])
        interp_E_pixMap[BBTemp][band]         = scp_interpolate.interp1d(lambdaMap[band][ypos,xpos][sel],E_pixMap[BBTemp][band][ypos,xpos][sel])

# Set-up common wavelength basis
d2cMaps_1B = funcs.load_obj('d2cMaps_band1B',path=d2cMapDir)
d2cMaps_3A = funcs.load_obj('d2cMaps_band3A',path=d2cMapDir)
ypos,xpos_1B   = funcs.detpixel_trace('1B',d2cMaps_1B,sliceID=d2cMaps_1B['nslices']/2,alpha_pos=0.)
ignore,xpos_3A = funcs.detpixel_trace('3A',d2cMaps_3A,sliceID=d2cMaps_3A['nslices']/2,alpha_pos=0.)
sel_1B     = (lambdaMap['1B'][ypos,xpos_1B]!=0)
sel_3A     = (lambdaMap['3A'][ypos,xpos_3A]!=0)

# print np.sort(lambdaMap['3A'][ypos,xpos_band3A][sel_band1B])[0],np.sort(lambdaMap['1B'][ypos,xpos_band1B][sel_band1B])[0]*2.
# print np.sort(lambdaMap['3A'][ypos,xpos_band3A][sel_band3A])[-1],np.sort(lambdaMap['1B'][ypos,xpos_band1B][sel_band1B])[-1]*2.

wvl_min,wvl_max         = np.sort(lambdaMap['3A'][ypos,xpos_3A][sel_3A])[5],np.sort(lambdaMap['1B'][ypos,xpos_1B][sel_1B])[-5]*2.
idx_wvl_min,idx_wvl_max = funcs.find_nearest(np.sort(np.flipud(lambdaMap['3A'][ypos,xpos_3A][sel_3A])),wvl_min),funcs.find_nearest(np.sort(np.flipud(lambdaMap['3A'][ypos,xpos_3A][sel_3A])),wvl_max)
common_wvl              = np.flipud(lambdaMap['3A'][ypos,xpos_3A][sel_3A])[idx_wvl_min:idx_wvl_max]
In [12]:
R_n1,R_n2 = {},{}
for relation in ['800K_600K','800K_400K','600K_400K']:
    # solve 2x2 system of radiometric equations
    Teff1,Teff2 = relation.split('_')[0],relation.split('_')[1]
    #-- coefficients
    a1 = interp_EXTSOURCE_pixMap[Teff1]['3A'](common_wvl)
    a2 = interp_EXTSOURCE_pixMap[Teff2]['3A'](common_wvl)
    b1 = interp_E_pixMap[Teff1]['3A'](common_wvl)
    b2 = interp_E_pixMap[Teff2]['3A'](common_wvl)
    c1 = interp_E_pixMap[Teff1]['1B'](common_wvl/2.)
    c2 = interp_E_pixMap[Teff2]['1B'](common_wvl/2.)
    
    R_n1[relation] = (-a1/c1 + a2/c2) / (-b1/c1 + b2/c2)
    R_n2[relation] = (-a1/b1 + a2/b2) / (-c1/b1 + c2/b2)

# use RSRF of band 3A as reference
fringe_img_3A,photom_img_3A = funcs.get_cdps('3A',cdpDir)[:2]

def tick_function(X):
    # for plotting wavelengths and wavenumbers on the same plot (two x-axes)
    V = X/2.
    return ["%.2f" % z for z in V]

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
axs1 = fig.add_subplot(111)
axs2 = axs1.twiny()
axs1.plot(lambdaMap['3A'][ypos,xpos_3A],(photom_img_3A*fringe_img_3A)[ypos,xpos_3A],label='RSRF 3A mixed orders')
for relation in ['800K_600K','800K_400K','600K_400K']:
    Teff1,Teff2 = relation.split('_')[0],relation.split('_')[1]
    axs1.plot(common_wvl,R_n1[relation],label='RSRF order 1 {}/{}'.format(Teff1,Teff2))
    axs1.plot(common_wvl,R_n2[relation],label='RSRF order 2 {}/{}'.format(Teff1,Teff2))
axs1.hlines(0,11.4,13.5,'k',linestyle='dashed')
axs1.vlines(12.18,-0.5,3.25,'r',alpha=0.4,linestyle='dashed')
axs1.set_ylim(-0.5,3.25)
axs1.set_xlabel('Wavelength [micron] n=1')
axs1.set_ylabel(r'Response $[(DN/sec)\; /\; (mJy/pix)]^{-1}$')
axs1.legend(loc='center left',fontsize=12)
axs2.set_xlim(axs1.get_xlim())
tickmarks = np.array([11.5,12.,12.5,13.,13.5])
axs2.set_xticks(tickmarks)
axs2.set_xticklabels(tick_function(tickmarks))
axs2.set_xlabel(r'Wavelength [micron] n=2')
plt.tight_layout()

Remarks:¶

  • The first spectral order (n=1) responses determined from the different pairs of observations are consistent.
  • The second spectral order (n=2) responses are less consistent compared to the first spectral order (n=1) responses.
